  • Constructor Details

    • Level

      public Level​(java.lang.String levelName, int levelIndex, java.util.List<java.lang.String> raw_level)
      Constructs the map for specified string listraw_level which contains the symbol of game objects, save the objects in two GameGrids. The diamonds will be stored in diamondsGrid and others will be stored in objectGrid.
      Parameters:
      levelName - the name of level
      levelIndex - the index of level
      raw_level - the string list of game map
      See Also:
      GameEngine.IsDebugActive(), GameGrid(int, int), GameGrid.PutGameObjectAt(GameObject, int, int), GameObject.FromChar(char)

    • IsComplete

      public boolean IsComplete()
      Judge whether this level is completed, use cratedDiamondsCount to store the completed diamonds, if the value of it is equals or larger than the numberOfDiamonds, then the level is completed.
      Returns:
      true if the level is completed; otherwise return false.
      See Also:
      GameGrid.GetGameObjectAt(int, int)

    • SaveGrid

      public static GameGrid SaveGrid​(Level level)
      This method is called when user wants to save the game grid. It puts the object in level to an empty grid.
      Parameters:
      level - the input level
      Returns:
      a game grid with objects in the level
      See Also:
      Level.LevelIterator, GameGrid
